                <h2>How I'm Moving from Financial Integrity to Technological Integrity</h2>
                <p>For years, I built a career on a foundation of discipline, risk mitigation, and strategic leadership. As a Team Leader and Manager in the finance and compliance sector, my work was all about structure. I led teams, streamlined processes with tools like Power Automate, and ensured adherence to complex regulatory frameworks like Anti-Money Laundering and Know Your Customer.</p>
                <p>There was a deep sense of accomplishment in a job well done, in the tangible results and the clear path of progression. But beneath the satisfaction of achievement, a different kind of ambition was growingâ€”a desire for a purpose that resonated more deeply with my values. I started to see the world's most critical challenges lying at the intersection of technology and ethics.</p>
                <p>This led to a strategic pivot. I am now leveraging my core experience in risk and compliance to address the challenging new domain of technological integrity, focusing on how AI is deployed ethically and responsibly.</p>
                
